Zero shot prompting: In Zero shot prompting, we don't give any example.
We give a direct command and expect the AI to know how to do it instantly based on its general knowledge. Simple,Straightforward tasks like basic translations or standard questions. 
E.g.,"Tell me the opposite 'Happy'." ( Output : Sad)

One Shot Prompting: In one shot prompting, we give only one example. 
We show the AI exactly one example of the desired format or style so it can mimic it. When you need the output to follow a specific structure or tone.
Good- Bad
Up-
Output: Down 

Few Shot Prompting:
In few shot prompting, we give AI two or more than two examples. We feed the AI multiple examples to help it recognize a complex pattern or a tricky rule before it answers.
It is used for complex tasks,strict formatting, or teaching the AI a unique logic. 

Apple:Fruit
Carrot: Vegetable
Chicken: Meat
Broccoli:
(Output: Vegetable)
